# VulnTrends local secrets
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your real values. The `.env`
# file is gitignored — your secrets never leave your machine.
#
# On GitHub Actions, the same variables come from the repository's
# encrypted secrets (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions) and
# are passed to the build step via the `env:` block in
# `.github/workflows/refresh-data.yml`.

# NVD/CVE API key — request at https://nvd.nist.gov/developers/request-an-api-key
# Without this key the NVD source is limited to 1 request per 6 seconds,
# which makes the data build take 10+ minutes.
NVD_API_KEY=

# Microsoft CVRF API key — request at https://portal.azure.com
# (the "MSRC Programmable Access" resource). Optional: without it
# the MSRC source returns an empty array and the pipeline falls
# back to NVD for Microsoft data.
MSRC_API_KEY=
